This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the problem of object detection in 3D point clouds, which is a central problem in many computer vision applications. It is also likely to belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as the problem of object detection in 3D point clouds is particularly relevant to autonomous navigation and housekeeping robots. The paper proposes a deep learning approach, which involves end-to-end training of a network, making it likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper introduces a new voxel feature encoding layer, which is a novel contribution to the field of deep learning, making it likely to belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, such as region proposal networks (RPNs), making it possible for it to belong to the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
